title: F1 Climbable — player can climb a climbable object
story: chord-f1-climbable
description: ADR-218 §1a (ratchet F2) — the `climbable` trait adjective composes
  ClimbableTrait, closing the object-`climbing` action gap. The ladder carries
  only the `climbable` adjective, so a successful `climb` proves the adjective
  alone made the object climbable.
---

# The climbable ladder is present and describable.
> examine ladder
[OK: contains "wooden ladder"]

# `climb` succeeds because `climbable` composed ClimbableTrait.
> climb ladder
[OK: contains "onto the ladder"]
